title: Bob Knight, legendary Indiana Hoosiers coach, dies at 83
description: Bob Knight, the longtime Indiana University basketball coach, died Wednesday at the age of 83, his family announced.

title: Johnson makes case to Senate GOP that Israel aid has to move before Ukraine funding
description: Newly-minted Speaker of the House Mike Johnson spoke with Senate Republicans Wednesday about his controversial Israel-only aid package in an effort to gain their support.

title: Republicans plan vote on push to expel George Santos from the House
description: The House will vote Wednesday night on a Republican-led resolution to expel George Santos

title: House to consider censure resolution against Tlaib over her criticism of Israel
description: The House of Representatives on Wednesday will consider a pair of censure resolutions against Democratic Rep. Rashida Tlaib and Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene.

title: Former officer to change plea to federal charges in Tyre Nichols' death: Attorney
description: Desmond Mills Jr., one of the five former Memphis police officers charged in the death of Tyre Nichols, plans to change his plea to federal offenses, his attorney said.

title: Firefighters battling to contain Southern California wildfire though many homes remain threatened
description: More than 1,200 firefighters are attacking a big Southern California wildfire, and fire officials say that effort has made inroads in containing the flames

title: WATCH:  Watch how this special therapy pony brings joy to elderly people’s bedsides
description: Sarah Woodland, owner of Dinky Ponies, says Poppy the pony has a “sixth sense” of empathy that makes her the perfect therapy animal to connect with elderly people.

title: Cooking spray burn victim awarded $7.1 million in damages after can 'exploded into a fireball'
description: A jury in Illinois has ordered Chicago-based Conagra Brands to pay $7.1 million to a Pennsylvania woman who was badly injured in 2017 when a can of cooking spray ignited in a commercial kitchen at her workplace and set her aflame

title: 1 dead, 1 trapped in building collapse at shuttered coal plant: Officials
description: One worker is dead and rescue efforts are underway to locate another after an 11-story building collapsed at a shuttered coal plant in eastern Kentucky, officials said.

title: Pilot indicted for allegedly threatening co-pilot with gun during flight
description: A former Delta Airlines pilot has been indicted for allegedly threatening his co-pilot with a firearm on an August 2022 flight. He will appear in court on Nov. 16.

title: Teachers kick off strike in Portland, Oregon, over class sizes, pay and resources
description: Teachers in Portland, Oregon, went on strike Wednesday, shuttering school for some 45,000 students in Oregon's biggest city

title: Collapse of Kentucky plant being demolished leaves 1 worker dead, another trapped
description: Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear says a man has died after he and a coworker were trapped beneath a collapsed 11-story building being demolished at an abandoned mine’s coal preparation plant

title: Cop who tased suspect several times as man begged him to stop charged with cruelty
description: Cop who tased suspect several times as man begged him to stop charged with cruelty

title: U.S. job openings rise slightly to 9.6 million, sign of continued strength in the job market
description: Employers posted 9.6 million job openings in September, up from 9.5 million in August and a sign that the U.S. job market remains strong in the face of higher interest rates

title: CDC report finds infant mortality rate has risen for the 1st time in 2 decades
description: A new CDC report published Wednesday found infant mortality rates in the U.S. rose 3% from 2021 to 2022, a small rise but the first year-over-year seen in two decades.

title: 'General Hospital' alum Tyler Christopher dead at 50
description: "General Hospital" alum Tyler Christopher, who played Nikolas Cassadine on the soap opera, has died at the age of 50.

title: 2 killed in Russian attacks in eastern Ukraine that also damage Kherson city center
description: Ukrainian officials say a Russian attack on Kherson has killed one person and caused serious damage in the city’s center

title: Fed expected to leave interest rates unchanged despite stubborn inflation
description: A surging economy has complicated the Fed's fight to cool price increases.

title: WATCH:  Smog blankets Beijing
description: China's capital, Beijing, is shrouded in some of the worst air pollution the region has experienced this year.

title: China keeps up military pressure on Taiwan, sending 43 planes and 7 ships near island
description: Taiwan says China has sent another 43 military aircraft and seven ships near the self-ruled island, the latest sign that Beijing plans no let-up in its campaign of harassment, threats and intimidation

title: Man arrested for pointing gun at 6-year-old boy's head over Halloween goody bag
description: A man has been arrested after allegedly pulling a gun on a 6-year-old and pointing it at his head over Halloween candy, police say.

title: Belarusians who fled repression face new hurdles as they rebuild their lives abroad
description: Hundreds of thousands of Belarusians who fled repression in their homeland face the prospect of having invalid documents after authoritarian President Alexander Lukashenko signed a decree halting passport renewals abroad

title: People of African descent still face discrimination and attacks: UN
description: The U_N_ body formed to promote respect for and protect people of African descent around the world says in its first report that they continue “to be victims of systemic racial discrimination and racialized attacks.”

title: Helicopters drop water on Oahu wildfire for 2nd day
description: Helicopters are battling a wildfire in remote mountainous area of Hawaii's Central Oahu as flames burn native koa and ohia trees

title: New speaker's Israel funding showdown with Biden, Democrats -- and Senate Republicans
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson is set to introduce a standalone bill providing more than $14 billion in aid to Israel -- but his bill is setting the stage for a showdown.

title: Donald Trump Jr. to testify in Trump Organization's $250 million fraud trial
description: The Trump Organization's $250 million fraud trial becomes a family affair Wednesday when Donald Trump Jr. becomes the first of Donald Trump's children to take the stand.

title: Senators question airline frequent flyer programs, citing 'unfair' practice claims
description: Two senators are asking U.S. regulators to address reports of "unfair" practices in airlines' frequent flyer and loyalty programs
